ENCORE WineASIO patch -- keep the backend sample rate instead of ASE_NoClock

Ported from shibco/ableton-linux patches/wineasio/0001-asio-keep-backend-sample-
rate-instead-of-ASE_NoClock.patch (shibco / shibacomputer, cade@parare.al) -- a
fix to GPL-2.0+ WineASIO's asio.c. Applies to WineASIO 1.3.0
(b5e668103ad13e6f51f4118ed7090592213e5ca2).

WineASIO cannot change the backend (JACK/PipeWire) graph rate; many machines run
a single fixed rate. Returning ASE_NoClock on a sample-rate mismatch is what the
ASIO spec suggests, but Ableton Live treats the refusal as fatal -- it throws out
of its OnSetSampleRate handler, the exception is uncaught, and Live dies during
startup, before its Preferences dialog exists, so the user can never reach the
control that would fix the rate. A fresh install lands in a permanent crash loop
(Live defaults to 44.1 kHz, PipeWire to 48 kHz). Instead, stay at the backend
rate and report success; hosts read the effective rate back with GetSampleRate
(Live does exactly that), so the engine runs at the graph's real rate.

diff --git a/asio.c b/asio.c
index 310b840..4d529a0 100644
--- a/asio.c
+++ b/asio.c
@@ -805,8 +805,29 @@ HIDDEN LONG STDMETHODCALLTYPE SetSampleRate(LPWINEASIO iface, double sampleRate)
 
     TRACE("iface: %p, Sample rate %f requested\n", iface, sampleRate);
 
-    if (sampleRate != This->host_sample_rate)
-        return -995;
+    if (sampleRate == This->host_sample_rate)
+        return 0;
+
+    /* The backend (JACK/PipeWire) owns the graph rate and a client cannot
+     * change it; on many machines the hardware has exactly one usable rate
+     * (the Steam Deck's codec runs at 48 kHz only, and forcing PipeWire to
+     * 44.1 kHz stalls the graph outright).
+     *
+     * Returning ASE_NoClock here is what the ASIO spec suggests, but Ableton
+     * Live treats the refusal as fatal: it throws out of its OSetSampleRate
+     * message handler, the exception goes uncaught, and Live dies during
+     * startup -- before its Preferences dialog exists, so the user can never
+     * reach the control that would fix the rate. A fresh install therefore
+     * lands in a permanent crash loop (Live defaults to 44.1 kHz, PipeWire to
+     * 48 kHz).
+     *
+     * Stay at the backend rate and report success instead. Hosts read the
+     * effective rate back with GetSampleRate -- Live does exactly that, and
+     * logs "Open: Used SampleRate: 48000" -- so the engine runs at the rate
+     * the audio graph is really using, at the correct pitch. */
+    WARN("host asked for %.0f Hz; the backend runs at %.0f Hz -- keeping the "
+         "backend rate (wineasio-clamp-sample-rate)\n",
+         sampleRate, This->host_sample_rate);
     return 0;
 }
 
